	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you are facing addiction — or you love someone who is — the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> You carry what most people never see: the shame, the relapse you swore wouldn't happen again, the isolation, the quiet fear that you might be beyond forgiveness. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for addiction," "verses for recovery," "overcoming addiction," or "is there hope for me" — the answer is not shame or willpower alone. It is the Father of the prodigal, who saw his child still far off and <em>ran</em> down the road to meet him. No lecture. No rejection. Only arms open.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not your addiction, and you are not beyond His reach — the Father runs down the road to meet the one coming home, exactly as you are.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight addiction carries`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel trapped, ashamed, or like you have failed too many times to be loved, you are not alone and you are not beyond hope. Millions are walking the same hard road — and millions more have found their way home. The numbers tell both halves of the truth.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `48.7 million`, label: `Americans (ages 12+) had a substance use disorder in the past year (SAMHSA NSDUH, 2022)` },
		{ value: `29.5 million`, label: `Americans (ages 12+) had an alcohol use disorder in the past year (SAMHSA NSDUH, 2022)` },
		{ value: `107,941`, label: `drug overdose deaths in the United States in 2022 (CDC, 2023)` },
		{ value: `1 in 4`, label: `adults who ever had a substance use problem are now in recovery — over 20 million Americans (NIDA / Recovery Research Institute)` },
		{ value: `94%`, label: `of people with a substance use disorder did not receive any treatment in the past year (SAMHSA NSDUH, 2022)` },
