	voiceHeading={`Bible verses for addiction and recovery: the Father's voice`}
	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for addiction and recovery in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your perfect Father, straight into the shame, the cycle, and the hope of coming home. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Luke 15:20`, slug: `luke`, ch: 15, text: `While he was still a long way off, his Father saw him and was filled with compassion; He ran to His child, threw His arms around him, and kissed him.`, note: `You do not have to make it all the way home on your own — the Father runs the rest of the road to meet you.` },
		{ ref: `Romans 8:1`, slug: `romans`, ch: 8, text: `So there is now no condemnation — none at all — for those who belong to your Father in Christ Jesus.`, note: `Shame says you are beyond forgiveness. Your Father says there is no condemnation left for you.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 5:17`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 5, text: `So if anyone is in Christ, there is a whole new creation: the old has gone, and look — the new has come.`, note: `You are not defined by who you were yesterday — in Him, your Father makes you new.` },
		{ ref: `John 8:36`, slug: `john`, ch: 8, text: `So if the Son sets you free, you will be free indeed — truly and completely free.`, note: `Real freedom is not something you earn through willpower — it is something He gives.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `Your Father is close to the brokenhearted, and He saves those who are crushed in spirit.`, note: `On the lowest day, He is not distant — He draws nearest to the ones most crushed.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 43:18-19`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 43, text: `Do not dwell on what is behind you. Look — I am doing a new thing! Now it springs up; do you not see it? I am making a way in the wilderness and streams in the wasteland.`, note: `Your past does not get the final word — your Father is already making a way through it.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:13`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `I can do all things through the One who strengthens me — your Father gives the strength for each step.`, note: `The strength for the next clean hour is not yours to manufacture alone — He supplies it.` },
		{ ref: `1 Corinthians 10:13`, slug: `1-corinthians`, ch: 10, text: `No temptation has overtaken you that is not common to humanity. And your Father is faithful — He will not let you be tempted beyond what you can bear, but will provide a way out.`, note: `In the moment of craving, He always makes a way out — you are not powerless and you are not alone.` },
		{ ref: `Joel 2:25`, slug: `joel`, ch: 2, text: `I will restore to you the years the locusts have eaten, says your Father — the years that addiction stole, I will give back.`, note: `The time you feel addiction has devoured is not lost forever — your Father promises restoration.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`Addiction promises relief and takes everything. Here is what your Father gives instead — for free, because you are already His.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `No condemnation, only welcome`, bodyHtml: `Shame says you have failed too many times. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/romans/8" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Your Father says there is no condemnation</a> for those who belong to Him — no probation, no list of conditions, only arms open.` },
		{ heading: `A fresh start, not a record`, bodyHtml: `You are not stuck as who you were yesterday: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/2-corinthians/5" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">in Christ you are a whole new creation</a> — the old gone, the new come, again and again as often as you need it.` },
		{ heading: `Strength for the next step`, bodyHtml: `You do not have to manufacture the willpower alone: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/philippians/4" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">your Father gives the strength</a> for each step, each hour, each day of recovery.` },
		{ heading: `A way out of the craving`, bodyHtml: `When the pull feels overwhelming, you are not powerless: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/1-corinthians/10" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">your Father always provides a way out</a> — He is faithful, even when you feel you are not.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for those facing addiction`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet God as a Father who runs to you, not a judge`, bodyHtml: `Most Bibles can read like a verdict. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> on. So instead of one more voice telling you to do better, you meet the One who saw His child still far off and ran down the road to meet him.` },
		{ heading: `It's free, with audio, for the moment the craving or shame hits`, bodyHtml: `No account, no purchase, no app. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — listen at 3 a.m. when the craving comes, on the way to a meeting, or on the hard day after a relapse. The Father's voice is there the moment you need it.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks straight to the shame`, bodyHtml: `Feeling beyond forgiveness? Trapped in the cycle? Wondering if there is any hope left? Start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> or learn to talk to Him with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — the Word meets you exactly where you are, with no condemnation.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`You are not your addiction, and you are not beyond His reach. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father who runs to meet you, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; George MacDonald, Charles Spurgeon, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel free the first time you read it. That is okay. The Father's love is not a hype feeling — it is a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that the addiction cannot uproot, and recovery is rarely a straight line. He is patient with every step.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I saw you while you were still a long way off, and I never stopped watching the road. I know the shame you carry, the relapse you swore wouldn't come, the cycle that has worn you down. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: you are Mine, and I am running toward you right now — not the cleaned-up you, not the recovered you. You.</p><p>You do not have to earn your way home or prove yourself before you come. Come as you are, today, exactly as you are. There is no condemnation waiting here — only My robe around your shoulders and a celebration that the one I love has been found. I am your Father, I am close to the brokenhearted, and nothing you have done can make Me stop running toward you."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for those facing addiction`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for everyone facing addiction — every person worn down by the cycle, and every family aching to bring someone home. Let them hear Your voice above the shame and the craving, and let them know they are not their addiction and not beyond Your reach. Meet them the way You met the prodigal — not with a lecture, but with arms thrown open while they were still far off.</p><p>Father, set them free. Give them strength for the next step and the next hour, provide a way out in every moment of temptation, and restore the years the locusts have eaten. Draw near to the brokenhearted and lift the crushed in spirit. We pray Your protection over them and over their families — from the enemy, from temptation and relapse, from isolation, and from the lie that they have run out of chances to be loved.</p><p>Let them know there is no condemnation in You, that in Christ they are a whole new creation, and that nothing can separate them from Your love. Surround them with people who point them to You and to the help they need. And may they wake every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father, who never stopped watching the road.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
